#---------------
For Class Files:
Use CamelCase:
#---------------
Capitalize the first letter of each word.
Example: MyClassFile.py
Reflect the Class Name:

-> If your class is named SearchWidget, the file can be named SearchWidget.py.

#-------------------
For Function Files:
Use Snake Case:
#-------------------

Use all lowercase letters with underscores to separate words.
Example: my_function_file.py
Reflect the Functionality:

-> If your file contains utility functions related to file operations, you might name it file_utils.py.
